      <accessrestrict id="aspace_7c86ac7ae6b447c6aee4d3ebfbc75211">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_f8fb8e7cd75ae3a20b1721654c61c49e">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Beers Family Papers (MS 789). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>
      </prefercite>
      <bioghist id="aspace_5de2aae8a434455e1702c40b1d6bf03d">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Nathan Beers (1753-1849): served in the Revolutionary War in the Governor's Second Company of Guards, attaining the rank of captain; from 1778-1783 acted as regimental paymaster; in 1783 entered the mercantile business.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_eff9cf00257cc4a2a60eed0420e03ac0">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Journal, military papers, and financial records relating to the American Revolution as kept by Nathan Beers, paymaster and clothier of a Connecticut regiment. Also in the collection is a bill issued to Isaac Beers, and an autograph album (1860) with the signatures of Jefferson Davis, James Buchanan, William H. Seward and others.</p>
      </scopecontent>
